== Tutorials & presentations

*At University of Innsbruck (May 2025)*

- #link("https://innsbruck-webscraping-part-1.etiennebacher.com")[Webscraping Part 1: static webscraping]: a tutorial on webscraping static pages with rvest.

- #link("https://innsbruck-webscraping-part-2.etiennebacher.com")[Webscraping Part 2: dynamic webscraping]: a tutorial on webscraping dynamic pages with RSelenium.

- #link("https://innsbruck-large-data-r-python.etiennebacher.com")[Handling large data in Python and R]: a tutorial on handling datasets with tens of millions of observations using Polars (and tidypolars) in Python and R.

*At LISER (2022-2024)*

- #link("https://www.rselenium-teaching.etiennebacher.com")[Webscraping with RSelenium]: a tutorial on performing webscraping with RSelenium, 100+ slides.

- #link("https://www.rselenium-teaching-short.etiennebacher.com")[Webscraping with RSelenium (short)]: a shorter version of the RSelenium tutorial, ~40 slides.

- #link("https://www.good-practices.etiennebacher.com")[Good practices for research with R]: a small list of what I consider to be good practices for reproducible research with R, ~40 slides.

- #link("https://www.handling-large-data.etiennebacher.com")[Handling large data with polars and tidypolars]: a brief introduction (not a tutorial) to the Python and R packages polars and tidypolars, ~30 slides.


== Tools (selection)

- #link("https://jarl.etiennebacher.com/")[Jarl]: a very fast R linter, written in Rust.

- #link("https://rpolars.github.io/")[polars]: port of the Rust/Python polars library to R.

- #link("https://tidypolars.etiennebacher.com")[tidypolars]: get the functionalities of Polars with the syntax of the tidyverse in R.

- #link("https://flir.etiennebacher.com")[flir]: efficiently rewrite patterns of R code.

- #link("https://altdoc.etiennebacher.com")[altdoc]: use docute, docsify, mkdocs or quarto to create a website for your R package.

- #link("https://prompter.etiennebacher.com")[prompter]: easily add tooltips to HTML elements in R Shiny applications, using hint.css under the hood.

- #link("https://conductor.etiennebacher.com")[conductor]: create tours in R Shiny applications using shepherd.js.

